<TITLE> PM returns </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 6 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina returned on Sunday from Geneva, Switzerland where she attended the third World Climate Conference. She reached Zia International Airport on a Biman Bangladesh Airlines plane at around 1pm. Cabinet members, chiefs of the armed forces and other top officials received her at the airport. Hasina went to join the five-day conference on Sept 1 and delivered her speech on Sept 4. The prime minister stressed the need for the $2 billion fund as compensation for the least developed countries to deal with the losses caused by the climate change. She called upon the donor agencies and rich nations to contribute to the fund. She also asked them to provide technical assistance to the LDCs. As many as 155 countries attended the conference. Foreign minister Dipu Moni, state minister for forest and environment Hasan Mahmud, the prime minister's information secretary Abul Kalam Azad and her daughter Sayma Wazed Putul accompanied Hasina to the tour. bd
